40 SECTION 2.
41 In accordance with the requirements of Article VII, Section II of the Constitution of the State
42 of Georgia, this Act shall not become law unless it receives the requisite two-thirds' majority
43 vote in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.
44 SECTION 3.
45 The election superintendent of Gordon County shall call and conduct an election as provided
46 in this section for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of the Gordon County
47 school district for approval or rejection. The election superintendent shall conduct that
48 election on the Tuesday following the first Monday in November, 2025, and shall issue the
49 call and conduct such election as provided by general law. The election superintendent shall
50 cause the date and purpose of the election to be published once a week for two weeks
51 immediately preceding the date thereof in the official organ of Gordon County. The ballot
52 shall have written or printed thereon the words:
53 "( ) YES Shall the Act be approved which increases the homestead exemption from
54 Gordon County school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes for
55 ( ) NO certain residents of that school district who are:
56 (1) Between 65 and 69 years of age to $50,000.00 of the assessed value
57 of such homestead;
58 (2) Between 70 and 74 years of age to $115,000.00 of the assessed value
59 of such homestead; and
60 (3) 75 years of age or older to $125,000.00 of the assessed value of such
61 homestead?"
62 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
63 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
64 such question are for approval of the Act, Section 1 of this Act shall become of full force and
65 effect on January 1, 2026. If the Act is not so approved or if the election is not conducted
