66 as provided in this section, Section 1 of this Act shall not become effective, and this Act shall
67 be automatically repealed on the 365th calendar day following the election date provided for
68 in this section. The expense of such election shall be borne by Gordon County. It shall be
69 the election superintendent's duty to certify the result thereof to the Secretary of State. The
70 provisions of this section shall be mandatory upon the election superintendent and are not
71 intended as directory. If the election superintendent fails or refuses to comply with this
72 section, any elector of the Gordon County school district may apply for a writ of mandamus
73 to compel the election superintendent to perform his or her duties under this section. If the
74 court finds that the election superintendent has not complied with this section, the court shall
75 fashion appropriate relief requiring the election superintendent to call and conduct such
76 election on the date required by this section or on the next date authorized for special
77 elections provided for in Code Section 21-2-540 of the O.C.G.A.
78 SECTION 4.
79 Except as otherwise provided in Section 3 of this Act, this Act shall become effective upon
80 its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law without such approval.
81 SECTION 5.
82 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
